once for all, let me tell thee and assure thee, young man, it’s better to 
sail with a moody good captain than a laughing bad one. So good-bye to 
thee—and wrong not Captain Ahab, because he happens to have a wicked name. 
Besides, my boy, he has a wife—not three voyages wedded—a sweet, resigned 
girl. Think of that; by that sweet girl that old man has a child: hold ye then 
